# Pre-Push CI Gate Verification

## Non-negotiable rule

**Do not run `git push` or open/update a PR until you have run the CI-equivalent checks locally and they pass.**

Pushing broken code wastes review time and blocks the merge queue. If you cannot run a check locally (missing Postgres, Redis), run every check you can and note the gap in the PR Testing section — but never skip `gofmt` or unit tests.

## Minimum local gate (every Go change)

Run from repo root (`ibex-harness/`):

```bash
# 1. Format — must produce no output
gofmt -l $(find services/proxy services/auth packages -name '*.go' 2>/dev/null | tr '\n' ' ')

# 2. Unit tests for touched packages
go test ./services/proxy/...
go test ./packages/ratelimit/...   # when ratelimit touched

# 3. Repo guards
make repo-guards
```

PowerShell gofmt check:

```powershell
Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter *.go services/proxy,services/auth,packages | ForEach-Object { gofmt -l $_.FullName }
```

## Proxy/auth milestone gate (when touching proxy or auth)

```bash
make proto-gen
go test -tags=integration ./services/proxy/...   # requires Postgres (5432 or 5433)
```

Set `POSTGRES_TEST_DSN` if not using default test compose port.

## CI jobs you must mirror before push

| CI job | Local equivalent |
| --- | --- |
| `golangci-lint` | `gofmt -l` on all touched `.go` files (gofmt is the common failure) |
| `go-services (proxy)` | `gofmt -l services/proxy/...` + `go test ./services/proxy/...` |
| `proxy-auth-smoke` | `go test -tags=integration ./services/proxy/...` |
| `proxy-agent-verify-smoke` | `go test ./services/proxy/internal/http/ -run AgentVerification` + integration agent tests |
| `CodeScene` | Keep functions ≤4 args, extract helpers, avoid duplicated metric blocks (see `21-complexity-management.mdc`) |

## When push is allowed

Only after:

1. All applicable commands above exit 0
2. You recorded what you ran in the PR Testing section
3. No known failing CI checks on the branch

If CI fails after push, fix locally, re-run the gate, then push the fix — do not iterate blindly on CI.
